  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2021-02-03",
    "date": "2021-03-11T15:34:43Z",
    "text": "Medical Debt Relief Act of 2021 \n\nThis bill modifies requirements related to the reporting of medical debt. Specifically, a consumer reporting agency is prohibited from adding medical debt information to a consumer credit report if the debt\n\n was fully paid or settled, or is less than a year old. Additionally, a debt collector must notify the consumer prior to reporting medical debt to a consumer reporting agency."
  },
